  ID: 631057a1-0221-4885-ba61-78b661b62b70
  Locus:
    Daily: March 4
  Source:
    Description: Rome, May 14, 1904
    Title: Letters to a Young Poet
Title: To Love
---
To love does not mean to surrender, dissolve and merge with another
person. It is the noble opportunity for an individual to ripen, to
become something in and of himself. To become a world in response to
another is a great immodest challenge that has sought him out and
called him forth.
